Best regards,

Dennis Brown

I hope this message finds you well. I wanted to bring to your attention a matter regarding an accumulated imbalance due to transportation from PNM, which currently stands at approximately 375,000 mmbtu. While we understand that discrepancies can occur, we believe it's essential to address this situation to ensure a balance in the total order.

I had a discussion with Chuck Thompson from PNM, and we both agreed that it would be best to avoid over-delivery until we can verify the measurements accurately. It's crucial that we maintain a balance to prevent further complications.

I would like to work with you and your team next week to resolve this matter amicably. Thank you for your understanding and cooperation.

Best regards,

text_raw:
Dear,

I hope this message finds you well. I wanted to discuss the current state of Enron and its potential impact on our work. It appears that the company is facing some challenges, with the stock prices continuing to decline and a significant note due soon. As such, there may be some concerns about the availability of collateral.

With that in mind, I would like to suggest that we explore all options to ensure that our work remains unaffected, including the possibility of Joe returning to work if needed. If things become more challenging, we could also consider the option of moving back to Omaha and living in a trailer by AKSARBEN.

I understand that this may be a difficult time, and I want to assure you that I am committed to working together to find the best solution for our team.

Best regards,
text:

If things become more challenging, we could also consider the option of moving back to Omaha and living in a trailer by AKSARBEN.



I understand that this may be a difficult time, and I want to assure you that I am committed to working together to find the best solution for our team.



Best regards,

text_raw: Hey there! Just wanted to give you a heads up that El Paso has declared an Unauthorized Overpull Penalty situation, which will be in effect until further notice. The pipeline will be limiting scheduled volumes at underperforming interconnects to ensure system integrity. This is likely due to the A/BC border constraint that began on Thursday due to maintenance on the TransCanada-British Columbia Line. As a result, NOVA has changed its imbalance tolerance range to +2%/-18% on Wednesday, and neighboring Westcoast has a +20%/0% tolerance in effect. Just wanted to keep you informed on the situation.
text: Hey there! Just wanted to give you a heads up that El Paso has declared an Unauthorized Overpull Penalty situation, which will be in effect until further notice. The pipeline will be limiting scheduled volumes at underperforming interconnects to ensure system integrity. This is likely due to the A/BC border constraint that began on Thursday due to maintenance on the TransCanada-British Columbia Line. As a result, NOVA has changed its imbalance tolerance range to +2%/-18% on Wednesday, and neighboring Westcoast has a +20%/0% tolerance in effect. Just wanted to keep you informed on the situation.

Hello,

I hope this message finds you well. I wanted to bring to your attention a matter regarding intercompany trades. It has come to my attention that these trades may not necessarily terminate upon bankruptcy, and while the parties may not have to perform, for valuation purposes, the market positions are not terminated until notice is sent. I have been in discussions with Jim and other colleagues to determine when it would be appropriate to officially terminate these trades.

I kindly request your assistance in addressing this matter as soon as possible. If you have any questions or concerns, please feel free to contact me at your convenience.

Thank you for your attention to this matter.

Best regards,

Elizabeth Sager
713-853-6349

Karen - RE the Q below -
Will I still receive severance if the company files bankruptcy?

text_raw:
Dear [Recipient's Name],

I hope this email finds you well. I wanted to touch base with you regarding the recent performance of the stock market. As you may have noticed, there has been some volatility in the market, with the NASDAQ down 10% today and the Dow down almost 5% at one point. The TSE also experienced a dip, with a low point of 770 to 8880.

I believe that this downturn may be due to a number of factors, including margin positions being squeezed out of tech stocks. However, I also wanted to share my perspective on some solid stocks that I believe are still worth considering. In particular, I would recommend looking into CSCO, LU, MSFT, and ENE, as they all look very promising.

If you have any questions or would like to discuss this further, please don't hesitate to reach out.

Thank you for your time and attention, and I look forward to hearing back from you.

Best regards,

[Your Name]

text_raw:
Hello Karen.
I received your question about severance pay in the event of employment termination. For your records, I'll repeat your question below:
"Will I still receive severance if the company files bankruptcy?"
To answer your question, it is unfortunately unlikely that severance payments would continue in the event of bankruptcy of the company. The general policy is that current or former employees of a bankrupt entity are considered as unsecured creditors, in line with other unsecured creditors. Due to this, employee claims will generally be represented through a court designated trustee. Please let me know if this answers your question, or if you need further information.

The general policy is that current or former employees of a bankrupt entity are considered as unsecured creditors, in line with other unsecured creditors. Due to this, employee claims will generally be represented through a court designated trustee. Please let me know if this answers your question, or if you need further information.

Subject: Cute story
Anyone who's been single and over the age of 18 can relate to this.
When I was younger I hated going to weddings ...it seemed that all of my
aunts and the grandmotherly types used to come up to me, poking me in the
ribs and cackling, telling me, 'You're next.'
? They stopped that crap after
I started doing the same thing to them at funerals.

text_raw:
Dear Lynn,

I hope this message finds you well. I wanted to update you on the latest developments regarding our home office setup.

I'm pleased to share that we have updated our Remedy system to prioritize support for our home office workers. Additionally, we have made it a priority to assign any requests to Glenn or Robert whenever possible. Speaking of which, I'm happy to report that Glenn was able to successfully install a modem in Shirley's machine.

However, we are still experiencing some issues with the CITRIX Server and VPN access. Our solution center team believes that the problem may be on the Road Runner side, and Jean McFarland is currently working on a resolution. Despite this challenge, I am glad to report that everyone has been able to work from home with little to no issues.

Thank you for your understanding and please don't hesitate to reach out if you have any questions or concerns.

Best regards,
John Buchanan

Hi there,

I wanted to share some information with you regarding recent market trends. On Friday, Brent experienced a significant decline and I believe this may be a good time to consider selling. In case it's helpful, I suggest looking into relative storage levels and price levels for all BTUs in 1998. Relationships on the lower end of the spectrum can be a bit unusual, so I recommend keeping a couple of graphs handy: one chart showing all stocks as a percentage of full capacity, and another displaying BTU equivalents. It might also be useful to compare the two graphs and examine any differences.

I apologize that I don't have this information readily available to send over. Unfortunately, connecting to the Houston drive through Enron systems can be quite time-consuming. Let me know if there's anything else I can assist you with.

Best regards,

Dear Brad,

I hope this message finds you well. I wanted to touch base with you regarding some updates on our ongoing projects. We will need to pull some of the WEB team members to work on the split of the NNG and TW data on the ADHOC database, due to security concerns. As a result, there may be some delays in starting the HotTap Redesign Project.

I wanted to make sure that you and your team are aware of these changes, and please let me know if you have any questions or concerns. Our goal is to minimize any negative impact and get back on track as soon as possible. We are hopeful that we will be able to pick up the effort at the beginning of February.

Thank you for your understanding and cooperation in this matter. I appreciate your time and attention.

Best regards,

I sincerely apologize for the delay, but I am pleased to inform you that our legal department has provided a revised version of your contract. Best regards,

Dave Fuller
Enron North America
505-464-3732
